MEMC’s SunEdison Unit Relocates to California for Tax Incentives

-- B y   E h r e n   G o o s s e n s
-- 
2011-10-10T21:13:03Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-10/memc-s-sunedison-unit-relocates-to-california-for-tax-incentives.html
MEMC Electronic Materials Inc. (WFR) ’s
solar project development unit SunEdison is moving its
headquarters to  California  from  Maryland  to take advantage of
state tax incentives.  SunEdison qualifies for California’s solar energy property
tax exclusion, which now covers sale-leaseback transactions, the
state’s Governor  Jerry Brown  said today in a statement.
SunEdison’s new headquarters will be in Belmont.  To contact the reporter on this story:
